Mamman Daura, a nephew to President Muhammadu Buhari, has reportedly been flown to the United Kingdom for urgent medical treatment, according to Sahara Reporters. The 79-year-old top confidant of the president was said to have been taken the UK in a private jet on Wednesday. He was said to have been experiencing respiratory difficulties with COVID-19 related symptoms since last Friday. Mamman Daura former is s member of the ‘Cabal’, influencing decisions at the seat of power. The former journalist is said to have had a history of renal crisis and had regularly visited the UK for medical checks.